// HOW SENTIMENT ANALYSIS WORKS:
// Every piece of text has an emotional tone — positive, negative, or neutral.
// This module scores text on a scale from -1 (very negative) to +1 (very
// positive) using a simple word-scoring approach.
//
// It works by looking up each word in a sentiment dictionary and averaging
// the scores.  Words like "great" and "excellent" score positive, while
// "terrible" and "broken" score negative.
//
// WHAT USES THIS:
//   svc-memory.js — tags memories with sentiment for recall prioritization
//
// EXPORTS:
//   analyzeSentiment(text)  → {score, label}
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
